    <detaileddescription>
<para>An abstract class from which a Poisson-like solver can inherit. Classes inheriting from this must implement a way to solve the following equation: (1) <formula id="374">$  L\phi = - \nabla \cdot (\alpha \nabla \phi) + \beta \phi = \rho $</formula>, in <formula id="7">$ \Omega$</formula>,</para>
<para><formula id="375">$  \phi = 0 $</formula>, on <formula id="376">$ \partial \Omega$</formula>,</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>IdxRangeLaplacian</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The index range on which the equation is defined. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>IdxRangeFull</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The index range on which the operator() acts. This is equal to the IdxRangeLaplacian plus any batched dimensions. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MemorySpace</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The space (CPU/GPU) where the Fields passed to operator() are saved. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>LayoutSpace</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The layout space of the Fields passed to operator(). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
